# ðŸ”¸ Graphql Queries x Resolvers

GraphQl queries with resolvers **get** (read data) a specific item - have parameter to handle.  
_Example: getting one item from all the products in the database_

## ðŸ”¹ Define a Query Resolver Schema

``` graphql
type Query {
    #<resolver-custom-name>(<param>: <type>): <type>
    productById(id: ID!): Product
}

```

## ðŸ”¹ Execute a Query Resolver

``` graphql
{
    #<resolver-custom-name>(<param>: <value>) {
       productById(id: 'zzzzz') {
           id
           title
           description
           price
       }
    }
}

```

graphql.query:
{
    productById(id:"shoesLucky42"){
        id
        title
        description
        price
        reviews {
            userId
            comment
            rating
            date
        }
    }
}

{
    productsByPrice(min: 1, max: 40){
        id
        title
        description
        price
        reviews {
            id
            rating
            comment
            userId
            date
        }
    }
}

{
    orderById(id: 1){
        id
        date
        total
        products {
            id
            quantity
            title
            price
        }
    }
}
